      <title>Increasing disk size at Virtual Box using GParted</title>
      <link>https://hellendev.com.br/docs/increase-disk-size/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 16 Jan 2025 11:24:08 -0300</pubDate>
      <guid>https://hellendev.com.br/docs/increase-disk-size/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;i-had-to-increase-my-vmbox-disk-size-heres-how-i-did-it&#34;&gt;I had to increase my VMbox disk size. Here&amp;rsquo;s How I did It&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-by-step-guide&#34;&gt;Step-by-step guide&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 - Go to the Virtual Media Manager of the VM you want to increase the disk size&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;file-tools-vmmanager&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://hellendev.com.br/images/file-tools-vmmanager.png&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2 - Find the disk you want to grow and double-click it&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;double-click-disk&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://hellendev.com.br/images/double-click-disk.png&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3 - At the end of the screen, drag the square to the right to increase its size.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;disk-size-increase&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://hellendev.com.br/images/disk-size-increase.png&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4 - Now, we will need to allocate this new value. If you turn on your VM and give a &lt;code&gt;df - h &lt;/code&gt; command, you&amp;rsquo;ll se the size remain the same&lt;/p&gt;</description>
